# Auth API Test Cases
# Base URL: http://localhost:5000

### ─────────────────────────────────────────
### TEST 1: Register — Valid Input (EXPECT: 201 success)
### ─────────────────────────────────────────
POST http://localhost:5000/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Aashish",
  "email": "test@test.com",
  "password": "123456"
}

### ─────────────────────────────────────────
### TEST 2: Login — Correct Credentials (EXPECT: 200 + JWT token)
### ─────────────────────────────────────────
POST http://localhost:5000/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "test@test.com",
  "password": "123456"
}

### ─────────────────────────────────────────
### EDGE CASE 1: Register — Duplicate Email (EXPECT: 400 error)
### ─────────────────────────────────────────
POST http://localhost:5000/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Aashish",
  "email": "test@test.com",
  "password": "123456"
}

### ─────────────────────────────────────────
### EDGE CASE 2: Login — Wrong Password (EXPECT: 400 error)
### ─────────────────────────────────────────
POST http://localhost:5000/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "test@test.com",
  "password": "wrongpassword"
}

### ─────────────────────────────────────────
### EDGE CASE 3: Register — Invalid Email Format (EXPECT: 400 validation error)
### ─────────────────────────────────────────
POST http://localhost:5000/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Aashish",
  "email": "not-an-email",
  "password": "123456"
}

### ─────────────────────────────────────────
### EDGE CASE 4: Login — Non-existent User (EXPECT: 400 error)
### ─────────────────────────────────────────
POST http://localhost:5000/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "ghost@nobody.com",
  "password": "123456"
}

### ─────────────────────────────────────────
### BONUS: Health Check (EXPECT: 200 + API running message)
### ─────────────────────────────────────────
GET http://localhost:5000/
